Parliament, Tuesday, 05 June 2018 – The Joint Committee on Ethics and Members’ Interests (the “Ethics Committee”) will today hold a media briefing to publish the Register of Members’ Interests for 2017. The Register is published to the public in order to ensure transparency of public representatives, public trust and confidence in Parliament. Details of the media briefing are as follows: Date: Tuesday, 5 June 2018
	Time: 13h30
	Venue: S12a, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CO-CHAIRPERSONS OF THE JOINT ETHICS COMMITTEE, MR AMOS MASONDO (NA) AND MR AUMSEN SINGH (NCOP) For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Malatswa Molepo (Mr)
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8438
	Cell: 081 512 7920
	E-mail: mmolepo@parliament.gov.za Bills can only be introduced in Parliament by Ministers, Deputy Ministers, parliamentary committees and individual MPs.Read more